Contributing to the Gluster Community
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

There are a variety of ways to contribute to the Gluster community.

Gluster Community Planning
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

We are planning some massive changes at Gluster.org, which will become
the home for GlusterFS users and developers, as well as project leaders
of related projects. If you have opinions about 'the way things oughta
be' then hit the link below.

*
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/GlusterPlanning[Gluster.org
Planning Doc] - Make the next version of Gluster.org all that it can be
* http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Swag[Swag
Suggestions] - Suggest inexpensive but meaninful swag that you would
enjoy receiving for your participation.

Developers
^^^^^^^^^^

If you're interested in extending GlusterFS, learning about it's
architecture or participating in the developer workflow, you'll want to
read this:

*
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Developers[Developers]
*
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Planning34[GlusterFS
3.4 Release Planning] - we recently gathered up core developers to
discuss planning the 3.4 release.
*
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Features[Features
in Development] - submit feedback on proposed features, or add your own.
*
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Backport_Wishlist[Backport
Wishlist] - bugs fixed in master you would like to see backported to a
previous release branch

